 Kingdom":"Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"okolo 1326–okolo 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"okolo 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"okolo 1380","1380":"1380","England":"Anglie, United Kingdom","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, Anglie","England, United Kingdom":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"omkring 1326–omkring 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"omkring 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"omkring 1380","1380":"1380","England":"England, United Kingdom","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"circa 1326–circa 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"circa 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"circa 1380","1380":"1380","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, England","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"about 1326–about 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"about 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"about 1380","1380":"1380","England":"England, United Kingdom","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"England","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Middle English <i>Engelond</i> ‘England’. It was probably a formal alternative to   English  , which is also well evidenced as a surname in England. These names may have been acquired by English landowners who moved in Norman social circles or who lived in a neighbouring country (Scotland, Wales, or Ireland), or by English merchants who traded abroad.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of various farmsteads so named, from Old Norse <i>eng</i> ‘meadow’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’.","Swedish: ornamental name with the same meaning as 2."],"variants":[{"name":"English","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Welsh: ethnic name from Middle English <i>English</i>, <i>Inglish</i>, <i>Inglis</i> ‘English’ (Old English <i>Englisc</i>), sometimes alternating with Anglo-Norman French <i>Engleis</i>, <i>Engles</i>, <i>Anglais</i>, <i>Angles</i> (Old French <i>Englois</i>). Compare   Inglis   and   England  . Among the aristocracy and upper gentry it marked out a man of English ancestry from one of Norman or continental origin. In counties bordering England with Scotland and Wales the name distinguished an Englishman from a Scot or a native Welshman on both sides of the border. The name may also have been acquired by English merchants who traded abroad or who lived and worked in a ‘French’ borough in England (one exclusively administered by Normans).","Irish: in Ireland, this name was used to denote an Englishman, often being adopted for Irish <b>Aingléis</b> ‘Englishman’ or through mistranslation for <b>Mac an Ghallóglaigh</b>, see   Gallogly   and   Golightly  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice of England was born about 1326, in England, United Kingdom. She married Thomas de Orchard in 1345, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1380, in her hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"umbes 1326–umbes 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"umbes 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"umbes 1380","1380":"1380","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"noin 1326–noin 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","1410":"1410","1397":"1397","Abt 1326":"noin 1326","1330":"1330","Abt 1380":"noin 1380","1380":"1380","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Orchard Portman, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Orchard Portman, Somerset, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1326–Abt 1380":"environ 1326–environ 1380","1330–1397":"1330–1397","1346–1410":"1346–1410","1326–1380":"1326–1380","1326":"1326","1346":"1346","